---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ProtocolFilter from '../../components/ProtocolFilter';
---

<Layout>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-8 md:px-12" style="padding-top: 5rem; padding-bottom: 5rem;">
    <!-- Section A: Main Text and CTA -->
    <section class="pb-16 space-y-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900">Healing Protocols for Parkinson's</h1>
      
      <div class="space-y-4 text-lg text-slate-600">
        <p>
          Parkinson's disease is best known for its motor symptoms, but the condition begins long before tremors appear. It develops as dopamine-producing neurons gradually deteriorate—yet research now shows this process involves far more than the brain alone.
        </p>
        <p>
          For many individuals, the earliest changes occur in the gut, the immune system, and the metabolic pathways that keep cells healthy. Understanding these deeper contributors helps identify therapies that address the root causes rather than just the symptoms.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200/60 bg-card text-card-foreground shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex flex-col space-y-1.5 p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold leading-none tracking-tight text-slate-900">What Drives Parkinson's Progression?</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 pt-0 space-y-4 text-lg text-slate-600">
          <p>Growing evidence suggests several interconnected factors may influence disease onset and progression:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Gut–brain axis disruption affecting nervous system signaling</li>
            <li>Microbiome imbalance, including loss of hydrogen-producing bacteria</li>
            <li>Insulin resistance in the brain ("type 3 diabetes")</li>
            <li>Mitochondrial dysfunction affecting cellular energy</li>
            <li>Heavy metal exposure (e.g., manganese, lead)</li>
            <li>Chronic infections in the gut or oral cavity</li>
            <li>Systemic inflammation and oxidative stress</li>
          </ul>
          
          <p>These elements do not cause Parkinson's on their own, but together they may accelerate progression—or offer targets for slowing it down.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200/60 bg-card text-card-foreground shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex flex-col space-y-1.5 p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold leading-none tracking-tight text-slate-900">A Smarter Way to Navigate Parkinson's Therapies</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 pt-0 space-y-4 text-lg text-slate-600">
          <p>No single treatment is a cure, but many therapies have meaningful evidence supporting improvements in motor symptoms, non-motor symptoms, mitochondrial function, inflammation, and quality of life.</p>
          
          <p>This site helps you explore these options more clearly by organizing them into three resource levels:</p>

          <div class="space-y-3 pl-4">
            <div>
              <strong class="text-slate-900">• Maximum Resources</strong><br/>
              Advanced or specialized therapies that may offer the strongest potential benefits.
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-slate-900">• Average Resources</strong><br/>
              Evidence-supported options accessible to most people.
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-slate-900">• Limited Resources</strong><br/>
              Low-cost, practical therapies you can start immediately.
            </div>
          </div>

          <p>You can also rank each protocol by:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Importance</li>
            <li>Cost</li>
            <li>Ease of implementation</li>
          </ul>

          <p>This makes it simple to build a customized plan based on your priorities and circumstances.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200/60 bg-card text-card-foreground shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex flex-col space-y-1.5 p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold leading-none tracking-tight text-slate-900">What You'll Find Inside Each Protocol</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 pt-0 space-y-4 text-lg text-slate-600">
          <p>Each protocol page includes:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>A clear explanation of the therapy</li>
            <li>How it supports brain and gut health</li>
            <li>Strength of scientific evidence</li>
            <li>Benefits</li>
            <li>Risks and contraindications</li>
            <li>Practical implementation tips</li>
            <li>Citations from peer-reviewed literature</li>
          </ul>

          <p>Our goal is to help you make confident, informed decisions—without the confusion or hype that often surrounds Parkinson's treatments.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <a 
        href="/pd/learn-more" 
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 hover:underline font-medium text-base"
      >
        Learn More About the Science
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="w-4 h-4"><path d="M5 12h14"></path><path d="m12 5 7 7-7 7"></path></svg>
      </a>
    </section>

    <!-- Section B: Protocol App -->
    <section class="border-t border-slate-200" style="padding-top: 4rem; margin-top: 3rem;">
      <ProtocolFilter client:visible />
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

